<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-08T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-08T16:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/348a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-08T17:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 8, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1085. Informed by <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SRB1">Stevens</persName> that he has sent to you terms for chartering
                                Dutch ships,<note n="1" xml:id="d509fn1">See telegram No. 6984, Mar.
                                    21, to the Ambassador in Great Britain, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1423">p. 1423</ref>.</note>
                                which terms have been agreed to by British Government, and that you
                                are awaiting instructions from Department before presenting these
                                terms to Foreign Office. You may present terms, and give wide
                                publicity to them.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>